Boil your #kettle{}. Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil) and add the @flaked almonds{25%g}. Toast until golden, shaking the pan occasionally, ~{2-3%mins}. Transfer to a #bowl{} and set aside (keep the pan!). Halve, peel and finely slice the @echalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled and finely sliced). Dissolve the @vegetable stock powder{1} in a #measuring jug{} with the @water for the stock{300%ml}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat and add half the shallot. Cook, stirring, until soft, ~{2-3%mins}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and then the vegetable stock. Bring to the boil, reduce the heat to medium-low and cover with a #lid{}. Cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%mins}.

> The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, remove the ends from the @courgette{1}(ends removed), halve lengthways and slice into 1cm thick half moons. Heat a splash of @oil{} in the now empty frying pan and add the remaining shallot. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3%mins}. Add the courgette, @dried oregano{1%tsp} and @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} and @red wine stock paste{2%tsp}. Bring to the boil, stirring to dissolve the stock pot, lower the heat and simmer until thick, ~{10%mins}.

While the stew cooks, drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{10%g}(roughly chopped) and @black olives{30}(roughly chopped). Zest the @lemon{1}(zested and lemon wedges reserved) then chop into wedges. In a small bowl, stir together the toasted almonds, parsley, olives and a good pinch of lemon zest. Season with plenty of @ground black pepper{}, taste and add more lemon zest if necessary.

When the stew has thickened mix in the butter beans. Add the @baby spinach{125%g} a handful at a time, stirring until wilted and heated through. Season to taste with @salt{} and pepper. Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the remaining lemon zest.

Serve the rice in #bowls{} topped with the butter bean stew and finished with a sprinkling of the almond salsa. Add the lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over. Enjoy!